						<summary>

						<p>On a boulder in a locality called Ēṇi.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">14th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It mentions Māchinamaleya son of Kaṇilakōja with the epithet Śri-Bēchōja Komara was the <hi rend="italic">prahārī</hi> (watchman) of the place. Karaḍikal and Mānuve are mentioned as boundaries.</p>						

						<p>It is in characters of the 14th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
